SIMPLE: publicness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Publicness
<hw>Pub"lic*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or
state of being public, or open to the view or notice of people at large;
publicity; notoriety; <as>as, the <ex>publicness</ex> of a
sale</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quality or state of belonging to the community;
<as>as, the <ex>publicness</ex> of property</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Public school</ent>⟦br⟧
